  • Classes in com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient.command.message used by com.discoverydns.dnsapiclient.command.message 
    Class and Description
    MessageAcknowledgeCommand
    Command sent from a DNSAPIClient to the DNSAPI server, to acknowledge a specific Message, in the Account's message queue on the server.
    MessageAcknowledgeCommand.Builder 
    MessageGetCommand
    Command sent from a DNSAPIClient to the DNSAPI server, to get the details of a Message.
    MessageGetCommand.Builder
    Builder used to build the desired command.
    MessageGetResponse
    Response object received by the DNSAPIClient from the DNSAPI server subsequently to the sending of a MessageGetCommand, describing the details of the retrieved Message.
    MessagePollCommand
    Command sent from a DNSAPIClient to the DNSAPI server, to poll for the oldest outstanding Message in the Account's message queue on the server.
    MessageRecord
    A Message is a notification from the DNSAPI server, for the targeted sponsor Account's Users, offering information about changes performed by the server on a related object in the system.
